The football-shaped area of regions II and III combined is the area of a sector of circle $B$ minus the area of a sector of circle $D$ plus the area of square $ABCD.$  Since $AB = 2,$ the radius of circle $B$ is $\sqrt{2},$ and the radius of circle $D$ is $2.$

[asy]
